This paper discusses a framework for verifying the fixity of archived web resources, which falls under the domain of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also addresses security concerns related to the integrity of archived resources, which is relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The proposed approaches involve storing and disseminating fixity information, which could be implemented using database technologies (cs.DB) and software engineering principles (cs.SE).
